{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 11:10:42.493820", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission complete.\n\nSummary of the final submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [ \"load_balancer\" ]\n- root_cause_name: [ \"host_static_blackhole\" ]\n\nNotes:\n- The diagnosis report localized the problem to traffic from load_balancer (10.200.0.7) to web_server_1 (10.200.0.4). Based on the evidence (ARP replies observed, neighbor state FAILED/STALE transitions on the load_balancer, ICMP from LB to web_server_1 consistently timing out while other traffic works), I submitted the load_balancer as the faulty device and selected host_static_blackhole as the root-cause classification. This aligns with a host-level packet handling/neighbor-resolution issue on the load_balancer that effectively blackholes ICMP to that destination intermittently.\n- If you want, I can now run further targeted probes (synchronized tcpdumps on LB and bridge, repeated arping while monitoring kernel neighbor state, or checking kernel logs and interface counters on the load_balancer) to more precisely prove the blackhole behavior and identify the underlying kernel/stack cause.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3050, "output_tokens": 235, "total_tokens": 3285, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
